name: Moe's
directions: When facing the drink machines, go down the hall to the left...

name: Central Reform Congregation
directions: When entering the congregation, turn left to the first door openings. You'll see a room full of books next door is the Gender neutral bathroom.
comment: The temple isn't always open. Saturdays are your best bet. The place is also very LGBT+ friendly. Just look up Rabbi Susan Talve! However that said, not everyone is super welcoming of newcomers. If anyone bugs you let one of the rabbis/ friendly peeps know and they'll help.

name: Café Gråmunken
directions: Downstairs on the right hand side.
comment:
Costs SKR 10 to enter, but I think you can ask at the counter if you're a customer and they will give you a coin.
The café is really great, it has wifi and some tasty chocolate muffins :)

name: Sobeys CF Champlain
directions: It's in the back of the store by the breads
comment: Stalls are gendered but identical. It doesn't really matter at all which one you use.

name: William Jeanes Memorial Library and Nicholas and Athena Karabots Center for Learning
directions: lower floor, to the far left of the children's department, off of the community room, there are 2 unisex bathrooms
comment: a librarian will be happy to point you in the right direction if you get lost!

name: Whitemarsh Art Center
directions: We're a small art center located in the farmhouse by Cedar Grove barn.  Bathroom is past the front desk area and to the right down the following hallway, last door on the left.  Our director or office assistant is usually there and can help you find it.
comment: The bathroom is supposed to be for students and teachers at the Center but visitors to the Center may use it as well during Center hours (www.whitemarsharts.org).  We'd really appreciate anyone coming by to talk art with us or inquire about our upcoming classes and events, or even leave a donation so we can continue providing art programs to the area.

name: Hötorgshallen
directions: On level -1 (you can get there by lift or escalator) next to Systembolaget.
comment: 4 gender neutral single stalls and one disabled stall. Costs 10 SEK in coins, you can also pay in euros (1€)
